Title: Inside Out - Official US Trailer
Comment: I just love this, what a creative take on human emotion!! I think it's so cool how they show the differences between how children and adults manage their emotions. As you get older, it can get easier to manage your emotions because you'll be more in tune with yourself and just what you're feeling. Dealing with things in a calm, rational manner is something that can unify differing emotions. That's why they look the same in the mom and dad's heads, but not the girl's. In adolescents, like Riley, there's more of a divide between differing emotions. Also, in this movie, I really like that they show that people can sometimes be primarily motivated by a certain emotion. The dad responds with anger while the mom responds with sympathy. It's not that they only feel sadness or anger, it's just that everybody has a certain emotion that can trigger a more effective response in a "fight or flight" situation.

Title: Inside Out - Official US Trailer
Comment:
Two things I noticed:

1. From what we can see of the mom's "memories" (those colored orbs in the background), she seems to have a pretty calm demeanor. I don't see a single red orb back there.
2. This is actually quite perfect because the emotions in the parents' minds are a well-oiled machine. They're generally on the same level with each other and everything's in control. In Riley's growing mind, however, her emotions seem to be having a hard time getting along and maintaining peace and understanding each other.

Pixar, this is why I love you again and again. :D
